se%20of%20Pakistanis%20and%20terming%20them%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bbiggest%20asset%20of%20India%26quot%3B%2C%20Dawn%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Pakistan%20daily%2C%20Mr%20Aiyar%2C%20while%20addressing%20an%20event%20in%20Lahore%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPakistanis%2C%20from%20my%20experience%2C%20have%20been%20the%20people%20who%20perhaps%20overreact%20to%20the%20other%20side.%20If%20we%20are%20friendly%2C%20they%20are%20over-friendly%2C%20and%20if%20we%20are%20hostile%2C%20they%20get%20overly%20hostile.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20the%20session%20titled%20'Hijr%20Ki%20Rakh%2C%20Visaal%20Kay%20Phool%2C%20Indo-Pak%20affairs'%2C%20on%20the%20second%20day%20of%20the%20Faiz%20Festival%20at%20Alhamra%20in%20Lahore%2C%20the%20former%20Union%20Minister%20shared%20his%20affection%20for%20Pakistan%20and%20its%20people%2C%20saying%20he%20had%20never%20been%20to%20a%20country%20where%20he%20had%20been%20welcomed%20with%20such%20open%20arms%20as%20he%20was%20in%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20diplomat%20recalled%20his%20posting%20in%20Karachi%20as%20consul%20general%2C%20saying%20everyone%20looked%20after%20him%20and%20his%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20has%20written%20about%20a%20number%20of%20incidents%20in%20his%20book%2C%20Memoirs%20of%20a%20Maverick%2C%20which%20shows%20Pakistan%20as%20a%20completely%20different%20country%20to%20what%20the%20Indians%20imagine.%20He%20said%20that%20goodwill%20was%20needed%20but%20instead%20of%20goodwill%2C%20there%20had%20been%20something%20opposite%20during%20the%20last%2010%20years%20since%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20first%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%26quot%3B%20Dawn%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20I%20ask%20the%20people%20(of%20Pakistan)%20is%20to%20remember%20that%20(PM)%20Modi%20has%20never%20received%20more%20than%20one-third%20of%20the%20votes%20but%20our%20system%20is%20such%20that%20if%20has%20one-third%20of%20the%20votes%2C%20he%20has%20two-thirds%20in%20the%20seats.%20So%20two-thirds%20of%20Indians%20are%20ready%20to%20come%20towards%20you%20(Pakistanis)%2C%26quot%3B%20Dawn%20quoted%20Mr%20Aiyar%20as%20saying%20at%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20his%20friend%2C%20former%20envoy%20Satindar%20Kumar%20Lambah%2C%20the%20Congress%20leader%20said%20he%20had%20written%20a%20book%20about%20how%20he%20served%20for%20better%20bilateral%20ties%20between%20the%20bitter%20neighbours%20under%20six%20different%20prime%20ministers%20during%20his%20career%20as%20a%20diplomat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20leader%20also%20reiterated%20his%20call%20to%20open%20communication%20channels%20between%20the%20two%20countries%2C%20saying%20the%20current%20regime%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20made%20it%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%26quot%3Bbiggest%20mistake%26quot%3B%20by%20refusing%20to%20hold%20dialogue%20with%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20five%20Indian%20high%20commissioners%20who%20served%20in%20the%20Congress%20government%20and%20the%20BJP%20government%20in%20Islamabad%20and%20all%20five%20of%20them%20unanimously%20agreed%20that%20whatever%20are%20our%20differences%2C%20we%20must%20engage%20with%20Pakistan%20and%20the%20biggest%20mistake%20that%20we%20made%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years%20was%20the%20refusing%20dialogue.%20We%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20conduct%20surgical%20strikes%20against%20you%20but%20we%20don't%20have%20the%20courage%20to%20sit%20across%20the%20table%20and%20talk%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Aiyar%20said%20at%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20he%20considered%20it%20%26quot%3Bsilly%26quot%3B%20to%20expect%20that%20the%20%26quot%3BHindutva%20establishment%26quot%3B%20in%20India%20would%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnder%20Hindutva%2C%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20imitate%20Pakistan%2C%20which%20became%20an%20Islamic%20republic.%20The%20Gandhi-Nehru%20answer%20to%20the%20Islamic%20republic%20was%20that%20they%20would%20not%20become%20a%20republic%20based%20on%20religion%20but%20a%20republic%20based%20on%20all%20religions.%20But%20their%20philosophy%20that%20lasted%20for%2065%20years%20was%20overthrown%20in%202014%20and%20for%20the%20next%20five%20years%20we%20are%20going%20to%20have%20the%20same%20mindset%20in%20Delhi.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20a%20minority%20opinion%20because%2063%20per%20cent%20of%20Indians%20have%20never%20voted%20for%20BJP%2C%26quot%3B%20Dawn%20quoted%20him%20as%20saying%20at%20the%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20civil%20society%20in%20both%20countries%20%26quot%3Bshould%20continue%20dialogue%20until%20the%20governments%20awaken%2C%20but%20for%20that%20neither%20Pakistan%20nor%20India%20were%20any%20help%20due%20to%20visa%20issues.%20He%20suggested%20that%20businessmen%2C%20students%20and%20academics%20should%20continue%20meeting%20outside%20India%20and%20Pakistan%2C%20bypassing%20the%20governments%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20remarks%20and%20the%20sentiments%20he%20articulated%20marked%20a%20striking%20divergence%20from%20India's%20official%20position%20on%20Pakistan%20across%20global%20forums--that%20%26quot%3Btalks%20and%20terror%20don't%20go%20together%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExternal%20Affairs%20Minister%20S%20Jaishankar%20had%20earlier%20said%20Pakistan's%20core%20policy%20has%20been%20to%20%26quot%3Buse%20cross-border%20terrorism%20to%20bring%20India%20to%20the%20table%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20India%20made%20that%20policy%20irrelevant%20by%20%26quot%3Bnot%20playing%20that%20game%20now%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20Pakistan%20was%20trying%20to%20do%2C%20not%20now%20but%20over%20multiple%20decades%2C%20was%20really%20to%20use%20cross-border%20terrorism%20to%20bring%20India%20to%20the%20table.%20That%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20was%20its%20core%20policy.%20We%20have%20made%20that%20irrelevant%20by%20not%20playing%20that%20game%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jaishankar%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20case%20that%20we%20won't%20deal%20with%20a%20neighbour.%20After%20all%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%2C%20a%20neighbour%20is%20a%20neighbour%2C%20but%20it%20is%20that%20we%20will%20not%20deal%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20terms%20that%20they%20set%20where%20the%20practice%20of%20terrorism%20is%20deemed%20as%20legitimate%20and%20effective%20in%20order%20to%20bring%20you%20to%20the%20table.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20press%20conference%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20SCO%20Summit%2C%20Mr%20Jaishankar%2C%20in%20a%20scathing%20takedown%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20had%20said%20%26quot%3Bvictims%20and%20perpetrators%20of%20terrorism%20can't%20sit%20together%20and%20that%20Pakistan's%20credibility%20was%20depleting%20faster%20than%20its%20forex%20reserves%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707715080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fr5m6h6ls_mani-shankar-aiyar-ani_625x300_31_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcongress-leader-mani-shankar-aiyar-calls-pakistanis-biggest-asset-of-india-sparks-row-5040571%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22No%20stranger%20to%20controversy%2C%20veteran%20Congress%20leader%20and%20former%20Union%20Minister%2C%20Mani%20Shankar%20Aiyar%20on%20Sunday%20triggered%20a%20fresh%20row%20after%20coming%20out%20in%20praise%20of%20Pakistanis%20and%20terming%20them%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bbiggest%20asset%20of%20India%26quot%3B%2C%20Dawn%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcongress-leader-mani-shankar-aiyar-calls-pakistanis-biggest-asset-of-india-sparks-row-5040571%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndt