20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGenerative%20AI%20technology%20has%20advanced%20so%20rapidly%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20that%20some%20experts%20are%20already%20worried%20about%20whether%20we've%20hit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-chatgpt-getting-close-peak-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%E2%80%9Cpeak%20AI.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finterview-salesforce-chief-scientist-richard-socher-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERichard%20Socher%2C%20former%20chief%20scientist%20at%20Salesforce%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20CEO%20of%20AI-powered%20search%20engine%20You.com%2C%20believes%20we%20still%20have%20ways%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20Harvard%20Business%20Review%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhbr.org%2Fpodcast%2F2024%2F02%2Fthe-science-of-making-truthful-ai%3Fab%3DHP-bottom-podcast-text-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epodcast%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%2C%20Socher%20said%20we%20can%20level%20up%20large%20language%20models%20by%20forcing%20them%20to%20respond%20to%20certain%20prompts%20in%20code.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20large%20language%20models%20just%20%E2%80%9Cpredict%20the%20next%20token%2C%20given%20the%20previous%20set%20of%20tokens%2C%E2%80%9D%20Socher%20said%20%E2%80%94%20tokens%20being%20the%20smallest%20data%20units%20that%20have%20meaning%20in%20AI%20systems.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESo%20even%20though%20LLMs%20exhibit%20impressive%20reading%20comprehension%20and%20coding%20skills%20and%20can%20ace%20difficult%20exams%2C%20AI%20models%20still%20tend%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhallucinate-cambridge-dictionary-word-of-the-year-artificial-intelligence-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehallucinate%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20phenomenon%20where%20they%20convincingly%20spit%20out%20factual%20errors%20as%20truth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that%E2%80%99s%20especially%20problematic%20when%20they%E2%80%99re%20posed%20with%20complex%20mathematical%20questions%2C%20Socher%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20offered%20an%20example%20a%20large%20language%20model%20might%20fumble%20on%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20gave%20a%20baby%20%245%2C000%20at%20birth%20to%20invest%20in%20some%20no-fee%20stock%20index%20fund%2C%20and%20I%20assume%20some%20percentage%20of%20average%20annual%20returns%2C%20how%20much%20will%20they%20have%20by%20age%20two%20to%20five%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20large%20language%20model%2C%20he%20said%2C%20would%20just%20start%20generating%20text%20based%20on%20similar%20questions%20it%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20in%20the%20past.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20actually%20say%2C%20'well%2C%20this%20requires%20me%20to%20think%20super%20carefully%2C%20do%20some%20real%20math%20and%20then%20give%20the%20answer%2C'%E2%80%9D%20he%20explained.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20you%20can%20%E2%80%9Cforce%E2%80%9D%20the%20model%20to%20translate%20that%20question%20into%20computer%20code%20and%20generate%20an%20answer%20based%20on%20the%20output%20of%20that%20code%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20more%20likely%20to%20get%20an%20accurate%20answer%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocher%20didn't%20offer%20specifics%20on%20the%20process%20but%20did%20say%20that%20at%20You.com%2C%20they've%20been%20able%20to%20translate%20questions%20into%20Python.%20Broadly%20speaking%2C%20programming%20will%20%E2%80%9Cgive%20them%20so%20much%20more%20fuel%20for%20the%20next%20few%20years%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20they%20can%20do%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocher%E2%80%99s%20comments%20come%20as%20the%20growing%20roster%20of%20large%20language%20models%20struggle%20to%20outsmart%20OpenAI%E2%80%99s%20GPT-4.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgemini-ultra-google-ai-smarter-than-openai-gpt-4-2023-12%5C%2