i-corporatisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIronically%2C%20on%20a%20day%20when%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fformer-pm-pv-narasimha-rao-chaudhary-charan-singh-and-dr-ms-swaminathan-to-get-bharat-ratna-pm-modi%2Farticleshow%2F107549332.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ebestowed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20highest%20award%20of%20the%20land%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%2C%20upon%20the%20late%20M.S.%20Swaminathan%2C%20farmers%20demanded%20the%20implementation%20of%20reforms%20he%20had%20advocated%20to%20uplift%20millions%20of%20struggling%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fpolicy%2Freport-summaries%2Fswaminathan-report-national-commission-farmers%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSwaminathan%252C%2520submitted%2520five%2520reports%2520through%2Cholistic%2520national%2520policy%2520for%2520farmers.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efarmers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20farmers%E2%80%99%20demands%2C%20both%20symbolically%20and%20practically%2C%20mirror%20the%20concerns%20of%20developing%20countries%20in%20the%20global%20farm%20trade.%20If%20the%20long-standing%20demands%20of%20the%20Indian%20farmers%20are%20seemingly%20buried%20under%20one%20pretext%20or%20the%20other%2C%20then%2C%20how%20can%20the%20Modi%20government%20effectively%20press%20its%20much-delayed%20demand%20for%20a%20permanent%20solution%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fpermanent-solution-for-public-stockholding-top-priority-for-india-9116333%2F%5C%22%3Epublic%20stockholding%3C%2Fa%3E%20(PSH)%20programmes%20for%20food%20security%2C%20in%20which%20the%20MSP%20is%20a%20critical%20component.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECome%20February%2026%2C%20more%20than%201%2C000%20delegations%20will%20gather%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20for%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organisation%E2%80%99s%20biennial%20trade%20ministerial%20conference.%20The%2013th%20ministerial%20conference%20(MC%2013)%20of%20the%20trade%20body%20will%20decide%20whether%20there%20is%20any%20future%20for%20the%20much-fragmented%20multilateral%20trading%20system.%20It%20will%20also%20indicate%20whether%20the%20demands%20of%20the%20developing%20countries%20in%20agriculture%20will%20ever%20be%20met.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20letter%20sent%20to%20trade%20ministers%20on%20January%2031%2C%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%20Director-General%2C%20Ngozi%20Okonjo-Iweala%2C%20who%20carries%20a%20dual-passport%20of%20Nigeria%20and%20the%20United%20States%2C%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%9COver%2050%20countries%20will%20be%20undergoing%20elections%2C%20including%20in%20very%20large%20democracies.%20People%20around%20the%20world%20are%20feeling%20anxious%20about%20their%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20and%20about%20the%20future.%20The%20WTO%20must%20be%20cognizant%20of%20the%20challenges%2C%20and%20we%20must%20do%20our%20part%20to%20contribute%20to%20reinvigorating%20growth%20and%20opportunities%20for%20people%20everywhere.%20MC13%20presents%20an%20immediate%20opportunity%20for%20ministers%20to%20show%20the%20world%20that%20it%20can%20get%20results%20on%20issues%20that%20matter%20for%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20there%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20sustained%20push%20on%20plurilateral%20issues%20that%20are%20being%20pushed%20by%20the%20US%2C%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20and%20China%2C%20without%20any%20prior%20multilateral%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwn.my%2Ftitle2%2Fwto.info%2F2024%2Fti240108.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econsensus%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20issues%20that%20concerns%20a%20large%20majority%20of%20people%20in%20the%20world%20is%20food%20security%20and%20the%20governments%E2%80%99%20ability%20to%20guarantee%20the%20provision%20of%20food.%20And%20there%20is%20certainly%20no%20bigger%20issue%20than%20providing%20bread%20on%20the%20table%20for%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20starving%20people.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20can%20only%20be%20done%20by%20changing%20existing%20global%20trade%20rules%20that%20were%20negotiated%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20globalisation%20in%20the%20mid-80s%20through%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wto.org%2Fenglish%2Fthewto_e%2Fwhatis_e%2Ftif_e%2Ffact5_e.htm%5C%22%3EUruguay%20Round%20commitments%3C%2Fa%3E.%20These%20rules%20are%20proven%20to%20be%20asymmetrical%20and%20unfair%20to%20developing%20countries%20through%20numerous%20studies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20urgency%20of%20the%20matter%2C%20the%20US%2C%20which%20continues%20to%20be%20the%20biggest%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20Uruguay%20Round%20commitments%2C%20along%20with%20the%20EU%2C%20Japan%2C%20Switzerland%2C%20Norway%2C%20and%20Canada%20among%20others%20are%20prepared%20to%20go%20to%20any%20extent%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwn.my%2Ftitle2%2Fwto.info%2F2024%2Fti240207.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eblock%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20attempts%20to%20rewrite%20those%20rules.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20permanent%20solution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgainst%20this%20backdrop%2C%20the%20constant%20claim%20of%20leading%20the%20Global%20South%20faces%20a%20test%20not%20just%20at%20home%20but%20abroad%20as%20well.%20It%20will%20become%20clear%20whether%20India%20fights%20for%20its%20farmers%20or%20yields%20ground%20to%20Uncle%20Sam%20on%20one%20of%20the%20most%20crucial%20issues%20for%20poor%20farmers%20in%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20issue%20lies%20the%20pursuit%20of%20a%20permanent%20solution%20for%20public%20stockholding%20programmes%20for%20food%20security%20purposes%20in%20developing%20countries.%20Washington%20remains%20violently%20opposed%20to%20the%20permanent%20solution%20as%20its%20powerful%20farm%20lobbies%20are%20unhappy%20with%20the%20existing%20peace%20clause%20or%20interim%20solution%20that%20was%20decided%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.wto.org%2Fdol2fe%2FPages%2FSS%2Fdirectdoc.aspx%3Ffilename%3Dq%3A%2FWT%2FMIN13%2F38.pdf%26Open%3DTrue%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2013%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20was%20later%20reinforced%20in%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wto.org%2Fenglish%2Fthewto_e%2Fminist_e%2Fmc9_e%2Fnov14stockholding_e.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2014%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20decided%20that%20the%20peace%20clause%20for%20exempting%20public%20stockholding%20programmes%20from%20legal%20scrutiny%20will%20continue%20as%20long%20as%20countries%20agreed%20to%20a%20permanent%20solution%20which%20ought%20to%20have%20been%20concluded%20in%202015%20and%20then%20deferred%20to%202017.%20The%20US%2C%20however%2C%20chose%20to%20block%20any%20decision%20for%20the%20past%20eight%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20discussions%20on%20a%20draft%20text%20issued%20by%20the%20chair%20from%20Turkey%20on%20January%2029%2C%20the%20US%2C%20along%20with%20supporters%20like%20Paraguay%2C%20proposed%20deleting%20the%20option%20to%20conclude%20an%20outcome%20on%20the%20permanent%20solution%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwn.my%2Ftitle2%2Fwto.info%2F2024%2Fti240205.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAbu%20Dhabi%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Instead%2C%20it%20suggested%20continuing%20discussions%20on%20several%20issues%20in%20the%20agriculture%20dossier%20until%20the%20WTO%E2%80%99s%2014th%20ministerial%20conference%20in%20Cameroon%20in%202026%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20reckons%20that%20the%20peace%20clause%20has%20enabled%20India%20to%20become%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20exporters%20of%20rice%2C%20an%20item%20on%20which%20India%20has%20also%20exceeded%20its%20de%20minimis%20limit%20of%2010%25%20during%202021%20and%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%5BUnder%20WTO%20rules%2C%20member%20countries%20are%20required%20to%20limit%20the%20amount%20of%20domestic%20support%20they%20provide%20to%20their%20agricultural%20producers%2C%20as%20excessive%20subsidies%20can%20distort%20international%20trade.%20The%20de%20minimis%20level%20represents%20a%20threshold%20below%20which%20subsidies%20are%20considered%20insignificant%20and%20do%20not%20count%20toward%20the%20total%20allowable%20support.%5D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20the%20PSH%20has%20helped%20India%20in%20addressing%20the%20provision%20of%20cereals%20like%20rice%20and%20wheat%2C%20which%20are%20procured%20through%20MSP%20and%20sold%20below%20MSP%20at%20lower%20prices.%20Without%20such%20a%20scheme%2C%20the%20poverty%20levels%20in%20India%2C%20which%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbesindia.com%2Farticle%2Fexplainers%2Fpoverty-rate-in-india%2F90117%2F1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%25202023%2520Multidimensional%2520Poverty%2520Index%2Cthe%2520increase%2520in%2520extreme%2520poverty.%5C%22%3Eamong%20the%20highest%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20would%20have%20shot%20through%20the%20roof.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20Brazil%20among%20others%20liken%20the%20PSH%20programme%20to%20a%20market%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bing.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3DUS%2Balleges%2BIndia%2Bprovides%2Bmarket%2Bprice%2Bsupport%2Bfor%2Brice%26qs%3Dn%26form%3DQBRE%26sp%3D-1%26ghc%3D1%26lq%3D0%26pq%3Dus%2Balleges%2Bindia%2Bprovides%2Bmarket%2Bprice%2Bsupport%2Bfor%2Brice%26sc%3D11-55%26sk%3D%26cvid%3DADBDC5E79C7A4F17915B62822B15DEF4%26ghsh%3D0%26ghacc%3D0%26ghpl%3D%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprice%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20support%20scheme%20and%20insist%20that%20it%20is%20a%20breach%20of%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20commitments.%20However%2C%20the%20calculation%20of%20the%20market%20price%20support%20programmes%20in%20the%20case%20of%20India%20is%20flawed%20as%20they%20are%20based%20on%20static%20assumptions%20like%20external%20reference%20price%20(ERP)%20based%20on%201986-88%20prices.%20Umpteen%20attempts%20to%20change%20the%20ERP%2C%20a%20demand%20developing%20countries%20have%20raised%20time%20and%20time%20again%20since%202015%2C%20are%20blocked%20by%20the%20US.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMany%20developing%20countries%2C%20particularly%20members%20of%20the%20G33%20countries%20led%20by%20Indonesia%20and%20the%20Africa%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twn.my%2Ftitle2%2Fwto.info%2F2023%2Fti231209.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGroup%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20have%20repeatedly%20demanded%20a%20permanent%20solution.%20However%2C%20they%20look%20up%20to%20India%20to%20do%20the%20heavy%20lifting%20because%20of%20the%20allegedly%20political%2Fdiplomatic%2Fnegotiating%20arm-twisting%20that%20goes%20behind%20the%20ministerial%20conferences.%20It%20has%20been%20seemingly%20established%20that%20the%20powerful%20members%20and%20the%20WTO%20Secretariat%20ensure%20that%20issues%20raised%20by%20the%20developing%20countries%20are%20often%20pushed%20to%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eback%20burner%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20groundwork%20for%20a%20permanent%20solution%20for%20PSH%20programmes%20for%20food%20security%20purposes%20has%20been%20laid%20ably%20by%20the%20Indian%20negotiators%2C%20who%20finally%20succeeded%20in%20including%20the%20first%20option%20in%20the%20chair%E2%80%99s%20draft%20text%20for%20the%20permanent%20solution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%2C%20it%20now%20depends%20on%20the%20political%20masters.%20Piyush%20Goyal%2C%20the%20commerce%20minister%2C%20is%20currently%20negotiating%20with%20farmers%20back%20home%20to%20ensure%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20bloated%20rhetoric%20championing%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20but%20concrete%20outcomes%20echoed%20through%20such%20pronouncements.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20track%20record%20for%20accomplishing%20its%20trade%20commitments%20appears%20somewhat%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2016%2F11%2Finsight%2Fwhat-happened-nairobi-and-why.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eappalling%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20The%20current%20finance%20minister%2C%20who%20was%20the%20commerce%20minister%20in%202015%2C%20has%20surrendered%20the%20ground%20to%20the%20US%20without%20a%20fight.%20With%20elections%20to%20be%20held%20in%20the%20next%20two-and-half%20months%2C%20it%20would%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%20if%20the%20current%20regime%20stands%20for%20its%20farmers%20or%20leaves%20them%20high%20and%20dry%20both%20domestically%20and%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707659736000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F01132506%2FAgriculture_main.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findias-wto-stance-on-farmers-will-be-a-test-of-its-rhetoric-of-championing-the-global-south%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20the%20upcoming%20WTO's%20biennial%20trade%20ministerial%20conference%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%2C%20it%20will%20become%20clear%20whether%20India%20fights%20for%20its%20farmers%20or%20yields%20ground%20to%20Uncle%20Sam%20on%20one%20of%20the%20most%20crucial%20issues%20for%20poor%20farmers%20in%20developing%20countries.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findias-wto-stance-on-farmers-will-be-a-test-of-its-rhetoric-of-championing-the-global-south%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Narendra%20Modi%3A%20A%20Pracharak%20Morphed%20into%20a%20Politician%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F24132337%2FModi-old-pics.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EExtracted%2C%20with%20permission%2C%20from%20Christophe%20Jaffrelot%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hurstpublishers.com%2Fbook%2Fgujarat-under-modi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGujarat%20Under%20Modi%3A%20Laboratory%20of%20Today%E2%80%99s%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20to%20be%20published%20on%2015%20February%202024%2C%20courtesy%20Hurst%20Publishers%2C%20London%2C%20%C2%A9%20Christophe%20Jaffrelot%2C%202024.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trajectory%20of%20this%20book%20has%20been%20atypical.%20I%20submitted%20the%20manuscript%20in%20late%202013%20in%20order%20to%20have%20it%20published%20before%20the%202014%20Indian%20elections.%20For%20publishers%2C%20election%20campaigns%20are%20usually%20a%20good%20time%20for%20selling%20political%20books.%20However%2C%20their%20legal%20advisors%20considered%20that%20this%20manuscript%20was%20%E2%80%9Chigh%20risk%E2%80%9D.The%20letter%20I%20received%2C%20summarising%20the%20legal%20assessments%2C%20claimed%20that%20some%20passages%20%E2%80%9Cmay%20be%20deemed%20as%20hurtful%20towards%20the%20people%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20containing%20an%20unyielding%20view%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%E2%80%9D.%20While%20the%20manuscript%20had%20been%20carefully%20copy-edited%2C%20I%20was%20asked%20to%20cut%20so%20many%20passages%20that%20I%20decided%20not%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20my%20publisher%2C%20Michael%20Dwyer%2C%20and%20I%20decided%20not%20to%20let%20this%20book%20die%20because%20it%20was%20our%20duty%20to%20testify%20and%20present%20facts%20which%20were%20gradually%20fading%20away%20%E2%80%93%20because%20of%20censorship%20and%20self-censorship%20%E2%80%93%20regarding%20the%20rise%20to%20power%20of%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20Gujarat%20and%20the%20specific%20political%20modus%20operandi%20he%20invented%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20has%20always%20claimed%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20apolitical%20CM%E2%80%9D.%20This%20claim%20extends%20back%20to%20his%20first%20faltering%20steps%20in%20the%20public%20arena%2C%20which%2C%20undeniably%2C%20have%20endowed%20him%20with%20a%20unique%20pedigree.%20But%20this%20claim%20needs%20to%20be%20scrutinised%20because%20it%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20the%20new%20chief%20minister%20had%20no%20ideology%3B%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20it%20reflected%20his%20sense%20of%20doctrinal%20purity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarendra%20Damodardas%20Modi%20was%20born%20on%2017%20September%201950%20in%20the%20small%20town%20of%20Vadnagar%20(Mehsana%20district).%20He%20hails%20from%20the%20low%20caste%20of%20Modh%20Ghanchis%20(oil%20pressers)%2C%20which%20was%20added%20to%20Gujarat%E2%80%99s%20Socially%20and%20Economically%20Backward%20Classes%20list%20in%201994%20and%20to%20the%20central%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBC)%20list%20in%201999.%20His%20father%20sold%20edible%20oil%2C%20but%20also%20had%20a%20tea%20stall%20where%20Narendra%2C%20according%20to%20most%20of%20his%20biographies%2C%20used%20to%20work%20as%20a%20child.%20He%20joined%20the%20local%20RSS%20shakha%20when%20he%20was%20seven%20or%20eight%20years%20old%20%E2%80%9Cbecause%20this%20was%20the%20only%20extra-curricular%20activity%20open%20for%20him%20outside%20his%20peer%20group%E2%80%9D.%20According%20to%20the%20biography%20of%20Modi%20by%20M.V.%20Kamath%20and%20K.%20Randeri%2C%20he%20very%20early%20on%20showed%20%E2%80%9Can%20inclination%20towards%20becoming%20a%20sanyasi%20%5Bworld%20renouncer%5D%E2%80%9D.%20Such%20a%20calling%20is%20not%20uncommon%20in%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS).%20M.S.%20Golwalkar%20himself%20renounced%20the%20world%20before%20becoming%20number%20two%20in%20the%20organisation.%20Like%20him%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20went%20to%20the%20Belur%20Math%2C%20headquarters%20of%20the%20Ramakrishna%20Mission%20in%20Calcutta%20(today%E2%80%99s%20Kolkata)%2C%20and%20then%20to%20the%20Himalayas.%20In%20an%20interview%20he%20gave%20to%20Nilanjan%20Mukhopadhyay%20he%20explained%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20went%20to%20the%20Vivekananda%20Ashram%20in%20Almora%2C%20I%20loitered%20a%20lot%20in%20the%20Himalayas.%20I%20had%20some%20influences%20of%20spiritualism%20at%20that%20time%20along%20with%20the%20sentiment%20of%20patriotism%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20all%20mixed.%20It%20is%20not%20possible%20to%20delineate%20the%20two%20ideas.%E2%80%9D%20This%20collapsing%20of%20religion%20and%20a%20certain%20political%20culture%20is%20typical%20of%20Hindu%20nationalists%20who%2C%20since%20Savarkar%2C%20look%20at%20India%20as%20their%20punya%20bhoomi%20(sacred%20land)%20and%20matri%20bhoomi%20(mother%20land).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20326px)%2085vw%2C%20326px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09203150%2F9781849044295-web.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22326%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09203150%2F9781849044295-web.jpeg%20391w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09203150%2F9781849044295-web-192x300.jpeg%20192w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696449%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22510%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChristophe%20Jaffrelot%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EGujarat%20Under%20Modi%3A%20Laboratory%20of%20Today%E2%80%99s%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EHurst%20Publishers%2C%202024%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20biographer%20of%20Modi%2C%20Kingshuk%20Nag%2C%20does%20not%20mention%20this%20episode%20at%20all%20but%20highlights%20the%20fact%20that%20Modi%20left%20Vadnagar%20in%201967%2C%20when%20he%20was%2017%20years%20old%2C%20to%20escape%20a%20child%20marriage%20that%20had%20been%20arranged%20years%20before.%20In%20this%20version%2C%20Modi%20went%20to%20his%20uncle%E2%80%99s%20place%20in%20Ahmedabad%20(about%20110%20km%20away)%20directly%20from%20his%20home%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20became%20a%20full-time%20RSS%20worker%20by%20the%20late%201960s%20or%20early%201970s.%20He%20then%20started%20living%20at%20Hedgewar%20Bhawan%20(RSS%20headquarters)%20in%20the%20residential%20area%20of%20Maninagar%20(Ahmedabad)%20and%20became%20the%20assistant%20to%20the%20prant%20pracharak%20in%20charge%20of%20Gujarat%20and%20Maharashtra%2C%20Lakshmanrao%20Inamdar%2C%20a%20former%20lawyer%20who%20regarded%20him%20as%20his%20manas%20putra%20(a%20son%20born%20out%20of%20the%20mind)%20and%20whom%20he%20regarded%20as%20his%20mentor.%20It%20seems%20that%20Modi%20became%20a%20pracharak%20as%20early%20as%201972.%20The%20next%20year%20he%20was%20involved%20in%20the%20Navnirman%20agitation%2C%20after%20being%20dispatched%20by%20the%20RSS%20to%20the%20ABVP%2C%20the%20Indian%20Student%20Association%2C%20then%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20this%20movement.%20Around%20that%20time%2C%20it%20seems%20that%20Modi%20registered%20as%20an%20MA%20student%20at%20Gujarat%20University%20after%20passing%20his%20BA%20as%20an%20external%20student%20of%20Delhi%20University.%20In%201974%20or%201975%2C%20he%20became%20close%20to%20one%20of%20his%20professors%2C%20Pravin%20Sheth%2C%20who%20writes%3A%20%E2%80%9CAs%20an%20external%20student%20of%20post-graduate%20programme%20in%20Political%20Science%20at%20Gujarat%20University%2C%20Modi%20used%20to%20come%20to%20me%2C%20collect%20reading%20material%20from%20me%2C%20grasp%20the%20matter.%20He%20applied%20them%20in%20examinations%20and%20achieved%20first%20class%20first.%20After%20acquiring%20good%20understanding%20of%20Political%20Sociology%20and%20Indian%20Politics%2C%20with%20his%20unique%20sense%2C%20he%20had%20applied%20the%20theory%20of%20Political%20Science%20in%20practice%20with%20appropriate%20adaptations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20was%20then%20absorbed%20by%20the%20Emergency%2C%20working%20underground.%20He%20was%20put%20in%20charge%20of%20disseminating%20information%2C%20including%20counter-propaganda%20against%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20(and%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s)%20dictatorial%20regime.%20He%20also%20took%20care%20of%20the%20families%20of%20those%20RSS%20leaders%20who%20were%20in%20prison%20and%20maintained%20%E2%80%9Clinks%20between%20Indians%20abroad%20and%20at%20home%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmediately%20after%20the%20Emergency%2C%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cassigned%20the%20role%20of%20key%20researcher%20for%20a%20resource%20book%20on%20the%20Emergency%E2%80%9D.%20This%20episode%20is%20important%20because%20it%20enabled%20Modi%20not%20only%20to%20interact%20with%20many%20politicians%2C%20but%20also%20to%20tour%20India.%20But%20he%20soon%20returned%20to%20his%20home%20state%20to%20pursue%20a%20career%20within%20the%20local%20RSS.%20As%20early%20as%201978%20he%20had%20been%20appointed%20vibhag%20pracharak%20(the%20head%20of%20RSS%20units%20in%20six%20districts)%2C%20and%20then%20sambhag%20pracharak%20(which%20involved%20the%20supervision%20of%20two%20vibhags%2C%20or%20divisions%2C%20those%20of%20Surat%20and%20Baroda).%20In%201981%2C%20he%20became%20prant%20pracharak%2C%20a%20role%20that%20consisted%20in%20coordinating%20various%20organisations%20of%20the%20Sangh%2C%20including%20the%20Vishva%20Hindu%20Parishad%20(VHP)%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Kisan%20Sangh%20and%20the%20ABVP%20throughout%20Gujarat.%20By%20the%20mid-1980s%2C%20he%20had%20been%20recognised%20as%20a%20skilled%20organiser%20and%2C%20when%20in%201986%20L.K.%20Advani%20became%20BJP%20president%2C%20he%20considered%20taking%20Modi%20on%20for%20party%20work.%20Deputed%20to%20the%20BJP%20in%201987%2C%20he%20became%20the%20sangathan%20mantri%20(organising%20secretary)%20of%20the%20Gujarat%20unit%20of%20the%20party.The%20organising%20secretaries%20had%20formed%20the%20backbone%20of%20the%20Jana%20Sangh%20since%20the%201950s%2C%20after%20Deendayal%20Upadhyaya%20created%20the%20post%20in%20the%201950s%20and%20occupied%20it%20for%20years%20at%20the%20national%20level.%20As%20the%20state%20party%20organiser-in-chief%2C%20Modi%20was%20the%20architect%20of%20a%20whole%20series%20of%20programmes%20in%20the%20form%20of%20%E2%80%9CYatras%E2%80%9D%20(literally%20pilgrimages%20or%20processions%2C%20but%20in%20practice%20mass%20demonstrations).%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20Nyay%20Yatra%20(Justice%20Pilgrimage)%20aimed%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdemand%20justice%20for%20Hindu%20riot%20victims%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20the%20Lok%20Shakti%20Yatra%20(People%E2%80%99s%20Power%20Pilgrimage)%20mobilised%20street%20protests%20against%20the%20liquor%20mafia%20in%20the%20Old%20City%20of%20Ahmedabad%20%E2%80%93%20a%20demonstration%20that%20exemplified%20the%20strategy%20of%20polarisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20Modi%20managed%20the%20Gujarat%20leg%20of%20Advani%E2%80%99s%201990%20Rath%20Yatra%2C%20which%20started%20from%20Somnath.%20Subsequently%2C%20his%20skills%20as%20an%20organiser%20were%20used%20for%20Yatra%20politics%20at%20the%20national%20level.%20In%20late%201991%2C%20he%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Ekta%20Yatra%2C%20which%20Murli%20Manohar%20Joshi%2C%20the%20BJP%20president%20who%20had%20just%20taken%20over%20from%20Advani%2C%20led%20from%20Kanyakumari%20to%20Srinagar%20in%20order%20to%20reaffirm%20the%20national%20unity%20of%20India.%20His%20colleagues%20in%20the%20BJP%20office%20in%20Delhi%20noticed%20that%20on%20this%20occasion%20%E2%80%9Che%20did%20not%20function%20the%20way%20a%20full-time%20RSS%20pracharak%20should.%20He%20was%20seen%20as%20projecting%20himself%20and%20seeking%20the%20limelight.%E2%80%9D%20Indeed%2C%20during%20the%20EktaYatra%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20only%20was%20Modi%20accompanying%20Joshiji%20on%20his%20vehicle%2C%20but%20would%2C%20at%20every%20stop%2C%20address%20the%20crowds%20along%20with%20the%20BJP%20president.As%20an%20organiser%20of%20the%20yatra%2C%20he%20should%20have%20consciously%20kept%20a%20low%20profile.%E2%80%9D%20Besides%20his%20taste%20for%20interacting%20with%20the%20Indian%20public%20which%20the%20EktaYatra%20revealed%2C%20it%20also%20afforded%20him%20a%20new%20opportunity%20to%20broaden%20his%20national%2C%20pan-Indian%20political%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20before%20becoming%20the%20main%20party%20organiser%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20Modi%20concentrated%20on%20one%20particular%20objective%20in%20the%201980s%3A%20the%20conquest%20of%20local%20power%20structures.%20He%20had%20concluded%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20route%20to%20Gandhinagar%20went%20through%20local%20power%20structures%20that%20had%20to%20be%20won%E2%80%9D.%20As%20mentioned%20above%2C%20the%20BJP%20took%20the%20municipality%20of%20Rajkot%20in%201983%20and%20that%20of%20Ahmedabad%20four%20years%20later%2C%20when%20Modi%20was%20in%20charge%20of%20all%20BJP%20election%20campaigns%20in%20the%20state%2C%20including%20local%20ones.%20These%20successes%20were%20achieved%20largely%20thanks%20to%20the%20growing%20political%20polarisation%20resulting%20from%20communal%20violence.Ahmedabad%20is%20a%20case%20in%20point.The%20BJP%20rose%20to%20power%20there%20after%20the%201985%20conflagration%2C%20before%20which%20Modi%20had%20told%20his%20professor%2C%20Pravin%20Sheth%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMuslims%20are%20spreading%20fear%20among%20the%20mixed%20localities%20of%20walled%20city%20areas%20in%20Ahmedabad.%20Their%20intention%20is%20to%20force%20evict%2070%25%20of%20Hindu%20population%20out%20of%20the%20pols%20%5Blanes%20of%20the%20Old%20City%20forming%20sub-local%20communities%5D%20in%20the%20walled%20city%20by%20spreading%20fear%2C%20and%20put%20the%20rest%20in%20minority%20so%20that%20they%20also%20sell%20their%20houses%20to%20Muslims%20and%20migrate%20to%20safer%20places%20in%20despair.%20Thus%2C%20they%20plan%20to%20convert%20the%20entire%20area%20of%20the%20walled%20city%20into%20a%20Muslim%20dominated%20town.%20But%20our%20RSS%20volunteers%20have%20reached%20there.%20We%20will%20educate%20Hindus%20about%20Muslim%20intent%2C%20try%20to%20raise%20their%20morale%20and%20prevent%20them%20from%20being%20evicted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sangh%20Parivar%20was%20indeed%20effective%20in%20Ahmedabad%2C%20as%20large%20numbers%20of%20Muslims%20fled%20during%20the%201985%20riots%20and%20sought%20refuge%20in%20the%20ghetto%20of%20Juhapura.%20But%20the%20polarisation%20strategy%20worked%20elsewhere%3B%20and%20this%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%20why%20in%201995%20the%20BJP%20won%20six%20municipal%20corporations%2C%20including%20that%20of%20Surat%20where%20the%20BJP%20took%20all%20the%20seats.The%20party%20also%20won%20a%20majority%20in%2018%20of%2019%20District%20Panchayat%20boards.%20Achyut%20Yagnik%20and%20Suchitra%20Sheth%20point%20out%20that%20in%20the%20rise%20to%20power%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20state%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20crucial%20factor%20was%20the%20Sangh%20Parivar%E2%80%99s%20penetration%20into%20the%20local%20power%20structures%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20which%20began%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20continued%20in%20the%201990s%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201995%2C%20Modi%20appeared%20as%20a%20major%20architect%20of%20the%20rise%20to%20power%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Gujarat%20after%20the%20party%20for%20the%20first%20time%20won%20a%20majority%20of%20seats%20in%20the%20state%20Assembly.%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20continued%20to%20rely%20on%20communal%20polarisation%2C%20a%20process%20that%20was%20nurtured%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%201985%20riot%2C%20by%20targeting%20the%20%E2%80%9CMuslim%20mafia%E2%80%9D%20of%20Abdul%20Latif.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20was%20also%20successful%20in%20eliminating%20political%20rivals%20and%20winning%20powerful%20patrons%20in%20Delhi%2C%20as%20the%201996%20episode%20of%20Advani%E2%80%99s%20election%20in%20Gandhinagar%20shows.The%20BJP%20president%20was%20then%20looking%20for%20a%20safe%20berth%2C%20given%20that%20in%201991%20he%20had%20won%20his%20New%20Delhi%20seat%20by%20a%20small%20margin%3A%20%E2%80%9Cit%20was%20Modi%20who%20suggested%20to%20Advani%20that%20he%20should%20contest%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20from%20Gandhinagar%20%E2%80%A6%20that%20was%20until%20then%20represented%20by%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20peer-turned-foe%20Shankarsinh%20Vaghela%20(he%20won%20in%201989).%20It%20was%20a%20masterstroke%20as%20BJP%20got%20charged%20up%20in%20the%20state%20and%20Vaghela%20was%20relegated%20to%20the%20fringes.The%20relationship%20grew%20with%20Advani%20frequently%20visiting%20Gujarat%20after%20becoming%20MP%20from%20the%20state.%E2%80%9D%20Modi%20had%20killed%20two%20birds%20with%20one%20stone%2C%20displaying%20a%20political%20acumen%20that%20is%20not%20usually%20the%20main%20hallmark%20of%20RSS%20pracharaks%2C%20who%20make%20a%20point%20of%20eschewing%20politics%20%E2%80%93%20by%20definition%2C%20a%20dirty%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGradually%2C%20Modi%20became%20a%20semi-public%20figure%2C%20to%20such%20an%20extent%20that%20he%20was%20called%20%E2%80%9Csuper%20chief%20minister%E2%80%9D%20after%20Keshubhai%20Patel%20formed%20the%20government%20and%20became%20its%20official%20head.%20He%20took%20part%20in%20cabinet%20meetings%20and%20remained%20in%20the%20room%20when%20senior%20bureaucrats%20came%20to%20report%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20for%20instance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Modi%20failed%20to%20keep%20the%20party%20united%2C%20despite%20this%20being%20a%20major%20responsibility%20of%20a%20sangathan%20mantri.%20After%20the%201995%20electoral%20triumph%2C%20Keshubhai%20Patel%20and%20Shankarsinh%20Vaghela%20were%20locked%20in%20fierce%20rivalry%20for%20the%20post%20of%20chief%20minister.%20In%20spite%20of%20his%20close%20long-term%20relationship%20with%20the%20latter%20(Vaghela%20was%2C%20like%20him%2C%20one%20of%20the%20few%20low-caste%20RSS%20veterans%20and%20party%20president%20when%20Modi%20was%20his%20secretary)%2C%20Modi%20threw%20his%20weight%20behind%20Patel%2C%20ensuring%20that%20Vaghela%20would%20get%20none%20of%20the%20spoils%20that%20were%20distributed%20to%20party%20workers.%20This%20move%20further%20alienated%20Vaghela%2C%20who%20created%20a%20difficult%20situation%20for%20Keshubhai%20Patel%20after%20defecting%20with%20%E2%80%9Chis%E2%80%9D%2047%20MLAs%20as%20mentioned%20above.%20After%20this%20episode%2C%20Patel%2C%20who%20came%20increasingly%20under%20the%20influence%20of%20Sanjay%20Joshi%2C%20another%20pracharak%20assigned%20to%20the%20BJP%20who%20was%20also%20a%20rival%20of%20Modi%2C%20persuaded%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20national%20leaders%20that%20Modi%20had%20to%20be%20banished%20from%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F09203846%2FNarendra_Modi_and_Prime_Minister_Atal_Bihari_Vajpayee_in_New_Delhi_in_October_12_2001.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22409%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-696450%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22304%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENarendra%20Modi%20with%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%2C%202001.%20Photo%3A%20PMO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENarendra%20Modi%20went%20to%20Delhi%20when%20he%20was%20appointed%20national%20secretary%20in%20November%201995%2C%20in%20charge%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%20Advani%2C%20who%20had%20become%20BJP%20president%20again%20in%201993%2C%20had%20been%20keen%20to%20promote%20him%20to%20that%20post%2C%20but%20his%20increasingly%20influential%20right-hand%20man%2C%20Pramod%20Mahajan%2C%20did%20not%20see%20eye%20to%20eye%20with%20Modi%2C%20and%20Modi%20had%20to%20spend%20most%20of%20his%20time%20in%20Chandigarh.%20However%2C%20when%20Kushabhau%20Thakre%2C%20another%20pracharak%20turned%20BJP%20cadre%2C%20became%20party%20president%20in%201998%2C%20Modi%20was%20promoted%20to%20the%20post%20of%20general%20secretary%20and%20started%2C%20from%20Delhi%2C%20to%20play%20a%20major%20role%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20organisation%20with%20official%20responsibilities%20for%20the%20states%20of%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20Chandigarh%20and%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Bharatiya%20JanataYuva%20Morcha%20(the%20youth%20wing%20of%20the%20party).%20He%20was%20retained%20in%20this%20capacity%20by%20Bangaru%20Laxman%20when%20the%20latter%20took%20over%20from%20Thakre%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20biographers%20M.V.%20Kamath%20and%20K.%20Randeri%20emphasise%20that%20by%20becoming%20Bharatiya%20sangathan%20mahamantri%2C%20Modi%20was%20following%20in%20the%20steps%20of%20three%20prestigious%20figures%3A%20Deendayal%20Upadhyaya%2C%20S.S.%20Bhandari%20and%20Kushabhau%20Thakre.%20However%2C%20none%20of%20them%20became%20public%20figures%20in%20the%20way%20he%20did%3A%20as%20organisers%2C%20they%20remained%20the%20power%20behind%20the%20throne%2C%20even%20though%20Upadhyaya%20and%20Thakre%20contested%20elections%20once%2C%20by%20default.%20Modi%2C%20on%20the%20contrary%2C%20had%20evinced%20some%20interest%20in%20the%20life%20of%20a%20politician.%20He%20liked%20public%20meetings%20and%20interacting%20with%20both%20the%20masses%20and%20the%20media.%20Other%20differences%20pertained%20to%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20tendency%20to%20side%20in%20faction%20fights%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20party%20unity%20and%20his%20abrupt%20behaviour%20with%20colleagues%2C%20two%20things%20that%20precipitated%20long-lasting%20antagonisms.%20Modi%20made%20two%20enemies%20in%20the%201990s%3A%20Shankarsinh%20Vaghela%20and%20Sanjay%20Joshi.%20Pravin%20Sheth%20attributed%20these%20developments%20to%20%E2%80%9Chis%20egoistic%20nature%20and%20abrasive%20behaviour%20with%20his%20fellow%20workers.%20Sometimes%20it%20appears%20that%20he%20has%20a%20Hubris%20complex.%20In%20this%20state%2C%20he%20tends%20to%20believe%20that%20his%20level%20of%20understanding%20is%20more%20than%20anyone%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20Modi%20played%20the%20politician%E2%80%99s%20game%20when%20it%20served%20his%20interests.%20Not%20only%20did%20he%20sidelineVaghela%20by%20suggesting%20to%20Advani%20that%20he%20stand%20for%20his%20constituency%2C%20but%20he%20also%20tried%20to%20dislodge%20Keshubhai%20Patel%20as%20chief%20minister%20of%20Gujarat.%20In%20his%20memoirs%2C%20Vinod%20Mehta%2C%20then%20editor-in-chief%20of%20Outlook%2C%20recalls%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20he%20was%20working%20at%20the%20party%20office%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20came%20to%20see%20me%20in%20the%20office.%20He%20brought%20along%20some%20documents%20that%20indicated%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20Gujarat%2C%20Keshubhai%20Patel%2C%20was%20up%20to%20no%20good.The%20next%20thing%20I%20heard%20was%20that%20he%20had%20become%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%20place%20of%20Keshubhai.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20Modi%20continued%20to%20present%20himself%20as%20an%20organisation%20man%20par%20excellence%20and%2C%20when%20Vajpayee%20asked%20him%20to%20take%20over%20from%20Keshubhai%20Patel%2C%20he%20replied%3A%20%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20not%20my%20work.%20I%20have%20been%20away%20from%20Gujarat%20for%20six%20long%20years.%20I%20am%20not%20familiar%20with%20the%20issues.%20What%20will%20I%20do%20there%3F%20It%20is%20not%20a%20field%20of%20my%20liking%20%5Bmy%20emphasis%5D.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20anyone.%E2%80%9D%20Although%20he%20liked%20mass%20meetings%2C%20Modi%20did%20not%20consider%20himself%20a%20politician.This%20factor%20was%20to%20play%20a%20role%20when%20he%20took%20his%20first%20steps%20as%20chief%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%2085%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%20knew%20that%20it%20would%20be%20a%20challenging%20task%20to%20arrest%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20declining%20trend%20before%20the%20state%20elections%20that%20were%20due%20to%20be%20held%20in%20February%202003.%20Just%20before%20his%20swearing-in%20as%20chief%20minister%20he%20told%20his%20colleagues%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20only%20500%20days%20and%2012%2C000%20hours%20before%20the%20next%20election%20for%20the%20state%20assembly.%E2%80%9D%20That%20the%20BJP%20was%20under%20such%20pressure%20probably%20explains%20why%20communal%20polarisation%20appeared%20particularly%20relevant%20to%20its%20pursuit%20of%20power%20in%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fchristophe-jaffrelot%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChristophe%20Jaffrelot%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20Senior%20Research%20Fellow%20at%20CERI-Sciences%20Po%2FCNRS%2C%20Paris%2C%20Professor%20of%20Indian%20Politics%20and%20Sociology%20at%20King%E2%80%99s%20College%20London%20and%20Chair%20of%20the%20British%20Association%20for%20South%20Asian%20Studies.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707658226000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F08%2F24132337%2FModi-old-pics.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fnarendra-modi-a-pracharak-morphed-into-a-politician%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Modi%20has%20always%20claimed%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20apolitical%20CM%E2%80%9D.%20This%20claim%20extends%20back%20to%20his%20first%20faltering%20steps%20in%20the%20public%20arena%2C%20which%2C%20undeniably%2C%20have%20endowed%20him%20with%20a%20unique%20pedigree.%20But%20this%20claim%20needs%20to%20be%20scrutinised.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fnarendra-modi-a-pracharak-morphed-into-a-politician%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ONGC%20Q3%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20shrinks%207.9%25%20to%20Rs%2010%2C748%20cr%20as%20production%20dips%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707658042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2016-12%2F23%2Ffull%2F1482514000-832.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fongc-q3-results-net-profit-shrinks-7-9-to-rs-10-748-cr-as-production-dips-124021100456_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22ONGC's%20total%20crude%20production%20dropped%20by%203.3%20per%20cent%20to%205.21%20million%20metric%20tonnes%20(MMT)%2C%20down%20from%205.39%20MMT%20in%20Q3%20FY23%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fongc-q3-results-net-profit-shrinks-7-9-to-rs-10-748-cr-as-production-dips-124021100456_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fongc-q3-results-net-profit-shrinks-7-9-to-rs-10-748-cr-as-production-dips-124021100456_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Fongc-q3-results-net-profit-shrinks-7-9-to-rs-10-748-cr-as-production-dips-124021100456_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pope%20and%20Milei%20meet%20as%20Argentina%20gains%20first%20female%20saint%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707657440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FC847%2Fproduction%2F_132617215_vaticanepaindex.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-68268257%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Argentine%20President%20Javier%20Milei%20had%20previously%20criticised%20the%20Pope's%20views%20on%20social%20justice.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A45%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-68268257%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-68268257.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-latin-america-68268257.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Electoral%20Bonds%20'Likely%20to%20be%20Sold'%20Ahead%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20Polls.%20Will%20the%20SC%20Act%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20clause%208%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%2C%202018%2C%20bonds%20can%20be%20issued%20for%2010%20days%20each%20in%20January%2C%20April%2C%20July%20and%20October%2C%20and%20an%20additional%2030%20days%20in%20the%20year%20of%20a%20general%20election.%20With%20general%20elections%202024%20just%20months%20away%2C%20the%2030-day%20period%20of%20issuance%20of%20bonds%20might%20be%20invoked%20again%2C%20even%20though%20the%20whole%20scheme%20has%20been%20challenged%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2002%2C%202023%2C%20the%20SC%20hearing%20in%20the%20matter%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheleaflet.in%2Fdonor-anonymity-versus-voters-right-to-know-supreme-court-reserves-judgment-in-electoral-bonds-case%2F%5C%22%3Ecompleted%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20judgment%20was%20reserved.%20In%20its%20order%20of%20November%202%2C%202023%2C%20the%20SC%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20that%3A%20%E2%80%9CIn%20any%20event%2C%20we%20now%20direct%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20shall%20produce%20up-to-date%20data%20until%2030%20September%202023%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20interim%20directions%20which%20were%20issued%20on%2012%20April%202019.%20The%20exercise%20shall%20be%20carried%20out%20on%20or%20before%2019%20November%202023.%20The%20data%20in%20sealed%20packet%20shall%20be%20handed%20over%20to%20the%20Registrar%20(judicial)%20of%20this%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETransparency%20activist%20Commodore%20Lokesh%20Batra%20filed%20an%20RTI%20with%20the%20Public%20Information%20Officer%20(PIO)%20of%20the%20ECI%20in%20the%20third%20week%20of%20November%202023%2C%20requesting%20copies%20of%20the%20complete%20set%20of%20documents%20including%20notings%20in%20the%20file(s)%2Ffolders%20on%20which%20Commission%20(EC)%20had%20processed%20the%20directions%20of%20the%20SC%20order%20of%20November%202%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommodore%20Batra%20brought%20to%20the%20notice%20of%20the%20PIO%20that%20he%20had%20filed%20a%20similar%20RTI%20request%20even%20after%20the%20SC%20order%20of%20April%2012%2C%202019%2C%20and%20had%20been%20provided%20complete%20file%20documents%20including%20a%20list%20of%20105%20political%20parties%20which%20provided%20details%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20sealed%20cover%20to%20the%20EC.%20Batra%20attached%20that%20list%20with%20his%20current%20RTI%20application%2C%20adding%20that%20in%20October%202023%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20in%20response%20to%20an%20RTI%20application%2C%20had%20said%20that%20only%2025%20political%20parties%20had%20opened%20accounts%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20encashing%20these%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommodore%20Batra%20mentioned%20that%20as%20per%20the%20existing%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%2C%20each%20Electoral%20Bond%20(EB)%20is%20a%20promissory%20note%20(akin%20to%20currency%20note)%20%E2%80%93%20hence%20the%20SBI%20would%20have%20details%20of%20EBs%20buyers%2Fdonors%20as%20per%20their%20KYC%20(Know%20Your%20Customer%20protocol).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESBI%20would%20also%20have%20details%20of%20%E2%80%98political%20party%20account%E2%80%99%20in%20which%20the%20said%20EB%20is%20redeemed%2C%20because%20each%20Electoral%20Bond%20(EB)%20has%20a%20hidden%20number%20verified%20by%20the%20SBI%E2%80%99s%20authorised%20branch%20before%20redemption%20in%20a%20political%20party%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98specific%20account%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20is%20opened%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20redeeming%20electoral%20bonds.%20Legally%2C%20the%20political%20party%20would%20not%20know%20the%20name%20of%20the%20donor%20based%20solely%20on%20the%20anonymous%20promissory%20note%20termed%20%E2%80%98electoral%20bond%E2%80%99%20it%20received.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20in%202019%2C%20Commodore%20Batra%20sought%20the%20%E2%80%98List%20of%20Political%20Parties%E2%80%99%20which%20had%20submitted%20EB%20details%20to%20ECI%20in%20sealed%20covers%2C%20in%20compliance%20with%20the%20letter%20from%20the%20Election%20Commission%20dated%20November%203%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20response%2C%20on%20December%2018%2C%202023%2C%20Binod%20Kumar%2C%20the%20public%20information%20officer%20of%20the%20Election%20Commission%2C%20denied%20information%20under%20the%20Section-8(1)(b)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20noteworthy%20the%20Section-8(1)(b)%20of%20the%20act%20mentions%20%E2%80%9Cinformation%20which%20has%20been%20expressly%20forbidden%20to%20be%20published%20by%20any%20court%20of%20law%20or%20tribunal%20or%20the%20disclosure%20of%20which%20may%20constitute%20contempt%20of%20court.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommodore%20Batra%20filed%20an%20appeal%20against%20this%20denial%20of%20information%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20not%20forbidden%20publication%20of%20the%20information.%20Commodore%20Batra%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20PIO%20had%20also%20failed%20to%20offer%20a%20cogent%20reason%20for%20denying%20the%20information.%20While%20the%20PIO%20under%20section%207(1)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005%20quoted%20Section-8(1)(b)%20for%20denial%20of%20information%2C%20he%20had%20failed%20to%20provide%20justification%20for%20arriving%20at%20the%20reason%20for%20denial%2C%20as%20envisaged%20under%20the%20Section%207(8)(i)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20this%20reporter%2C%20Commodore%20Batra%20noted%20that%20two%20days%20after%20the%20SC%20reserved%20judgment%2C%20on%20November%204%2C%202023%2C%20the%20government%20announced%2015%20days%20of%20sale%20of%20Electoral%20Bonds%20from%20November%206-20%2C%202023.%20Electoral%20bonds%20were%20sold%20again%20for%2010%20days%20in%20January%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20apex%20court%20directed%20the%20ECI%20to%20produce%20up-to-date%20data%20until%20September%2030%2C%202023%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20interim%20directions%20issued%20on%20April%2012%2C%202019%2C%20it%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20bonds%20have%20been%20sold%20already%20for%20a%20period%20of%2045%20days%20after%20September%2030%2C%202023.%20(10%20days%20in%20October%2C%2015%20days%20in%20November%202023%20and%2010%20days%20in%20January%202014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Electoral%20Bond%20scheme%20is%20problematic%20for%20several%20reasons%2C%20with%20the%20potential%20to%20kill%20democracy%20by%20offering%20undue%20advantage%20to%20the%20party%20in%20power%20%E2%80%93%20between%20March%202018%20and%20September%202023%2C%20the%20bonds%20were%20sold%20in%2030%20phases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20bonds%20sold%20are%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20each%20%E2%80%93%20clearly%2C%20these%20bonds%20are%20becoming%20the%20major%20source%20of%20electoral%20funding%2C%20and%20are%20being%20purchased%20by%20the%20very%20rich%2C%20or%20corporate%20players%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20average%20Indian.%20Only%200.0001%25%20of%20the%20bonds%20were%20in%20the%20denomination%20of%20Rs%201%2C000.%20The%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitical-pulse%2F57-vs-10-bjp-vs-congress-share-in-electoral-bond-funds-9007429%2F%5C%22%3Evast%20majority%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20these%20bonds%20(57%25)%20also%20go%20to%20the%20party%20in%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20a%20question%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20on%20February%205%2C%202024%2C%20Pankaj%20Chaudhary%2C%20Union%20Minister%20of%20State%20for%20Finance%20answered%20that%20Electoral%20Bonds%20worth%20Rs16%2C518%20crore%20had%20so%20far%20been%20purchased%20from%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%20The%20government%20had%20paid%20SBI%20Rs%208.57%20crore%20as%20commission%2C%20and%20Security%20Printing%20and%20Minting%20Corporation%20of%20India%20Limited%20had%20received%20Rs%201.90%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20the%20ordinary%20Indian%20bears%20this%20expense%20that%20the%20government%20shoulders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20response%2C%20the%20Union%20minister%20explained%20that%20the%20objective%20of%20the%20scheme%20is%20to%20ensure%20that%20%E2%80%9Cclean%2C%20tax%20paid%20money%20is%20coming%20into%20the%20system%20of%20political%20funding%20through%20proper%20banking%20channel.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3EHowever%2C%20as%20has%20been%20speculated%2C%20since%20the%20bonds%20are%20anonymous%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20for%20them%20to%20change%20hands%20several%20times%20before%20being%20submitted%20to%20a%20political%20party%20for%20encashment%20%E2%80%93%20who%20can%20guarantee%20that%20black%20money%20is%20not%20turned%20white%20through%20this%20scheme%2C%20as%20a%20man%20holding%20a%20bond%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20value%20could%20sell%20it%20to%20someone%20else%20at%2C%20say%2C%20Rs%201.2%20crore%2C%20in%20exchange%20for%20the%20favour%20of%20turning%20Rs%2020%20lakh%20of%20black%20money%20white%3F%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Economic%20Affairs%20has%20referred%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Fgovt-spent-rs-13-50-cr-to-operate-electoral-bond-scheme-9089091%2F%5C%22%3Ecorrespondence%3C%2Fa%3E%20showing%20that%2018%25%20GST%20is%20charged%20on%20the%20bonds%2C%20but%20reimbursed%20by%20the%20government%20to%20SBI%3B%20what%20this%20means%20is%20that%20the%20burden%20is%20borne%20entirely%20by%20the%20Indian%20citizen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Electoral%20Bond%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20through%20amendments%20to%20law%20that%20lifted%20restrictions%20on%20the%20amount%20of%20donations%20that%20private%20firms%20could%20make%3B%20Election%20Commission%2C%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice%20in%202017%2C%20underlined%20that%20the%20proposal%20to%20lift%20the%20limit%20on%20donations%20from%20companies%20%E2%80%9Copens%20up%20the%20possibility%20of%20shell%20companies%20being%20set%20up%20for%20the%20sole%20purpose%20of%20making%20donations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirms%20no%20longer%20need%20to%20declare%20which%20party%20they%20are%20contributing%20to%3B%20transparency%20in%20fund-raising%20by%20political%20parties%20is%20compromised%20as%20no%20reporting%20of%20contributions%20received%20is%20expected%20from%20the%20political%20parties.%20Donations%20can%20also%20be%20received%20from%20foreign%20companies%20having%20majority%20stake%20in%20Indian%20firms%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Ccould%20lead%20to%20Indian%20policies%20being%20influenced%20by%20foreign%20companies.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20does%20not%20rule%20in%20this%20matter%20with%20some%20urgency%2C%20the%20Centre%20may%20declare%20another%20round%20of%2030-day%20issuance%20of%20the%20bond%2C%20in%20different%20phases%2C%20ahead%20of%20general%20elections%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERosamma%20Thomas%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.counterview.net%2F2024%2F02%2Fwill-more-electoral-bonds-be-sold-ahead.html%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20Counterview.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707656408000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-likely-to-be-sold-ahead-of-lok-sabha-polls-will-the-sc-act%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20does%20not%20rule%20in%20this%20matter%20with%20some%20urgency%2C%20the%20Centre%20may%20declare%20another%20round%20of%2030-day%20issuance%20of%20the%20bond%2C%20in%20different%20phases%2C%20ahead%20of%20general%20elections%202024.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-likely-to-be-sold-ahead-of-lok-sabha-polls-will-the-sc-act%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Herbert%20Wigwe%3A%20Nigerian%20bank%20chief%20killed%20in%20US%20helicopter%20crash%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A17076554