wareness%20and%20provide%20training%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCurrently%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20working%20on%20a%20proposal%20to%20present%20to%20my%20university%20to%20initiate%20a%20program%20where%20individuals%20can%20come%20and%20learn%20how%20to%20make%20chairs%20and%20collaborate%20with%20me%20to%20create%20more%20furniture.%20This%20approach%20will%20allow%20me%20to%20train%20craftsmen%20in%20producing%20sustainable%20yet%20modern%20furniture%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETo%20view%20Ankit%E2%80%99s%20patent%2C%20visit%20this%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsearch.ipindia.gov.in%2FDesignQRStatus%2FPDF_Viewer.aspx%3FAppNo%3DMzk1MTU0LTAwMQ%3D%3D%26CNo%3DMTQ5NTI0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Elink%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you%20wish%20to%20get%20in%20touch%20with%20Ankit%2C%20You%20can%20reach%20him%20at%209879262737%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20%3Cem%3EAll%20pictures%20credit%3A%20Ankit)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707402725000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fabcf-6-1707399873.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D341205%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ankit%20Kumar%20Changawala%20from%20Veer%20Narmad%20South%20Gujarat%20University%2C%20recently%20patented%20a%20chair%20crafted%20from%20Bambusa%20bamboo%2C%20a%20locally%20abundant%20variety%20of%20South%20Gujarat%2C%20to%20promote%20the%20use%20of%20bamboo%20in%20furniture%20making.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A37%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bhumi%20Pednekar%E2%80%99s%20Bhakshak%3A%20How%20A%20TISS%20Team%20Blew%20The%20Lid%20Off%20Bihar%20Shelter%20Home%20Abuse%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20trailer%20for%20%E2%80%98Bhakshak%E2%80%99%20opens%20with%20a%20poignant%20scene%20depicting%20young%20girls%20residing%20in%20a%20shelter%20home%20in%20Bihar.%20Starring%20Bhumi%20Pednekar%2C%20Aditya%20Srivastava%2C%20and%20Sanjay%20Mishra%2C%20the%20film%20delves%20into%20the%20harrowing%20narrative%20inspired%20by%20the%20Muzaffarpur%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F308756%2Fmanila-bachan-recovery-journey-from-sexual-abuse-bipolar-disorder-video%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshelter%20home%20abuse%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20reverberated%20across%20the%20nation%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Bihar%20MLA%20Brajesh%20Thakur%20and%2011%20others%20currently%20serve%20a%20life%20sentence%20for%20their%20involvement%20in%20the%20appalling%20sexual%20assault%20of%20numerous%20minor%20girls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20tragic%20episode%20came%20to%20light%20through%20a%20social%20audit%20report%20conducted%20by%20a%20dedicated%20team%20of%20researchers%20from%20Koshish%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Field%20Action%20Project%20focusing%20on%20homelessness%20and%20destitution%20at%20the%20Tata%20Institute%20of%20Social%20Sciences%20(TISS).%20Over%20a%20span%20of%20six%20months%2C%20commencing%20in%20October%202017%2C%20a%20team%20of%20seven%20diligently%20surveyed%20more%20than%20110%20institutions%20either%20operated%20or%20supported%20by%20the%20Bihar%20Government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20primary%20aim%20of%20the%20social%20audit%20was%20to%20assess%20the%20functioning%20of%20these%20institutions%2C%20gauge%20the%20well-being%20of%20their%20residents%2C%20and%20identify%20gaps%20in%20the%20implementation%20of%20welfare%20schemes%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20care%20provided%2C%20the%20findings%20were%20nothing%20short%20of%20alarming%20for%20the%20researchers.%20They%20uncovered%20widespread%20instances%20of%20sexual%20abuse%20and%20violence%20in%20nearly%2017%20institutions%2C%20revealing%20a%20deeply%20disturbing%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20submitted%20by%20TISS%20to%20the%20Bihar%20Government%20in%20May%202018%20marked%2017%20institutions%20as%20%E2%80%98grave%20concern%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20required%20immediate%20attention.%20One%20of%20these%20institutions%20was%20Balika%20Grih%20(girl%E2%80%99s%20shelter%20home)%20run%20by%20Brajesh%20Thakur%E2%80%99s%20NGO%20Seva%20Sankalp%20Evam%20Vikas%20Samiti.%20The%20TISS%20researchers%2C%20led%20by%20Mohd%20Tarique%2C%20found%20that%20the%20girls%20in%20this%20home%20were%20sexually%20abused%20and%20assaulted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20investigation%20by%20the%20police%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F313961%2Flawyer-helps-child-sexual-abuse-victims-win-compensation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedical%20examination%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2034%20girls%20at%20the%20home%2C%20between%20the%20ages%20of%207%20and%2017%2C%20were%20sexually%20assaulted.%20The%20case%20was%20then%20transferred%20to%20the%20CBI%20and%2020%20people%20were%20charged%20in%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prime%20accused%2C%20Thakur%2C%20who%20ran%20other%20shelter%20homes%20too%2C%20was%20convicted%20on%20multiple%20grounds%20of%20rape%2C%20gangrape%20(Section%20376(d)%2C%20IPC)%2C%20criminal%20conspiracy%2C%20aggravated%20sexual%20assault%20under%20Section%206%20of%20the%20POCSO%20Act%2C%20and%20offences%20under%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20spoke%20to%20Mohd%20Tarique%20about%20how%20the%20TISS%20unearthed%20this%20heinous%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20social%20audit%20that%20exposed%20an%20appalling%20case%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%202560px)%20100vw%2C%202560px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fshutterstock_259928615_11zon-1707462732-scaled.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Representational%20image%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fshutterstock_259928615_11zon-1707462732-scaled.jpg%202560w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fshutterstock_259928615_11zon-1707462732-300x199.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fshutterstock_259928615_11zon-1707462732-500x332.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fshutterstock_259928615_11zon-1707462732-768x510.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fshutterstock_259928615_11zon-1707462732-1536x1020.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fshutterstock_259928615_11zon-1707462732-2048x1360.jpg%202048w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fshutterstock_259928615_11zon-1707462732-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-341267%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221700%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERepresentational%20image%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETISS%20was%20working%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F337399%2Fbihar-ias-officer-anshuman-raj-cracked-upsc-cse-without-coaching-success-story%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBihar%20Government%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20knowledge%20partner%20for%20the%20social%20welfare%20department.%20The%20then%20Principal%20Secretary%2C%20Department%20of%20Social%20Welfare%2C%20Atul%20Prasad%2C%20asked%20the%20team%20to%20conduct%20a%20social%20audit%20of%20all%20the%20institutions%20as%20he%20felt%20that%20there%20were%20lapses%20in%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20same.%20As%20only%20a%20social%20audit%2C%20which%20involves%20speaking%20to%20the%20people%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20would%20uncover%20the%20true%20picture%2C%20it%20was%20decided%20that%20the%20team%20should%20conduct%20a%20detailed%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20institutions%20included%20adoption%20agencies%2C%20children%E2%80%99s%20homes%2C%20short-stay%20homes%20for%20women%2C%20old%20age%20homes%2C%20and%20more.%20Initially%2C%20only%20institutions%20run%20by%20NGOs%20were%20to%20be%20covered%2C%20but%20later%20Government-run%20homes%20were%20also%20included%20in%20the%20ambit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20really%20helped%20the%20team%2C%20according%20to%20Tarique%2C%20was%20the%20methodology%20they%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHaving%20worked%20with%20the%20homeless%20for%20over%20two%20decades%2C%20I%20knew%20how%20we%20needed%20to%20approach%20and%20speak%20to%20the%20residents%20of%20such%20homes.%20We%20had%20strict%20rules%20when%20we%20entered%20each%20institution%20and%20spoke%20separately%20to%20the%20chiefs%2C%20staff%20members%2C%20and%20residents%2C%20and%20conducted%20a%20physical%20check%20of%20each%20facility%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Tarique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERight%20from%20the%20time%20they%20entered%20a%20home%2C%20they%20looked%20for%20non-verbal%20signs%2C%20which%20said%20more%20than%20words.%20They%20gauged%20the%20situation%20from%20the%20atmosphere%20at%20each%20institution.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20they%20found%20children%20sitting%20very%20quietly%2C%20in%20an%20organised%20manner%2C%20with%20fear%20in%20their%20eyes%2C%20it%20was%20a%20red%20flag%2C%20says%20Tarique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20did%20not%20allow%20any%20staff%20members%20to%20join%20when%20they%20conducted%20focus%20groups%20with%20the%20residents%2C%20be%20they%20children%20or%20elders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20to%20win%20the%20trust%20of%20the%20children%20in%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time.%20We%20did%20not%20allow%20any%20staff%20members%20inside%20when%20we%20spoke.%20We%20did%20not%20accept%20any%20refreshments%20when%20we%20entered.%20In%20fact%2C%20if%20staff%20members%20tried%20to%20delay%20our%20meeting%20with%20the%20residents%20by%20offering%20snacks%2C%20it%20was%20also%20a%20sign%20of%20something%20amiss%20for%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Tarique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20staff%20tried%20to%20keep%20interrupting%20in%20the%20pretext%20of%20some%20refreshments%20while%20they%20spoke%20to%20the%20residents%2C%20that%20too%20was%20a%20sign%20of%20alarm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%2C%20according%20to%20the%20social%20worker%2C%20was%20not%20acting%20immediately%2C%20based%20on%20the%20concerns.%20%E2%80%9CFirst%2C%20the%20child%20will%20test%20you%20by%20sharing%20a%20minor%20incident.%20If%20you%20go%20and%20question%20the%20staff%20immediately%2C%20the%20child%20will%20be%20reprimanded%20and%20won%E2%80%99t%20trust%20you.%20It%E2%80%99s%20only%20when%20they%20trust%20you%20that%20they%20will%20feel%20comfortable%20sharing%20the%20graver%20incident.%20If%20we%20get%20into%20the%20mode%20of%20fixing%20things%2C%20we%20might%20lose%20out%20on%20the%20more%20serious%20incident%20that%20the%20child%20wanted%20to%20report%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20adopted%20a%20balanced%2C%20strategic%20approach%2C%20where%20being%20neutral%20was%20key.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChildren%20seldom%20share%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F340517%2Fmansi-poddar-psychologist-therapist-childhood-abuse-trauma-molestation-domestic-violence%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincidents%20of%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%20openly%2C%20according%20to%20him.%20They%20tried%20to%20create%20an%20environment%20that%20encouraged%20children%20to%20come%20forward%20and%20speak.%20%E2%80%9CChildren%20shared%20that%20another%20child%20has%20been%20abused.%20They%20will%20always%20use%20another%20person%E2%80%99s%20name%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20they%20conducted%20focus%20groups%2C%20children%20who%20wished%20to%20speak%20alone%20did%20so.%20It%20was%20through%20this%20approach%20that%20they%20found%20alarming%20signs%20at%20the%20Balika%20Grih%20in%20Muzaffarpur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20observed%20the%20non-verbal%20communication%20between%20the%20staff%20members.%20At%20these%20places%20that%20they%20marked%20%E2%80%98grave%E2%80%99%2C%20they%20found%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20fear%20and%20the%20air%20of%20something%20being%20hidden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20over%20six-month%20audit%20across%2038%20districts%2C%20they%20finally%20submitted%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20dreadful%20situation%20at%20the%20Balika%20Gruh%2C%20which%20was%20a%20state-run%20home%2C%20they%20found%20that%20it%20was%20being%20run%20in%20a%20questionable%20manner.%20They%20also%20found%20that%20the%20girls%20were%20locked%20up%20in%20their%20rooms%20and%20had%20no%20access%20to%20open%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20escalated%20their%20fears%20and%20recommended%20immediate%20further%20probe.%20The%20Bihar%20Police%20then%20filed%20an%20FIR%20at%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20police%20station%20in%20Muzaffarpur%20in%20May%202018%20and%20named%2011%20people%2C%20including%20Brajesh%20Thakur.%20A%20medical%20report%20found%20that%20%E2%80%9C34%20of%20the%2044%20girls%20at%20the%20home%20were%20drugged%20and%20raped%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20intervened%20and%20transferred%20the%20case%20to%20the%20CBI%2C%20which%20charged%2020%20people%2C%20including%20nine%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20girls%20were%20shifted%20to%20different%20homes%20soon%20and%2017%20of%20them%20were%20sent%20to%20Bengaluru%20to%20do%20hotel%20management.%20A%20report%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20found%20that%2017%20of%20those%2034%20girls%20have%20built%20their%20lives%20and%20are%20working%20in%20hotels%20a